All Implemented Interfaces:
ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable
public class Catalog
extends JComponent

This class contains the catalog tree and associated property panels. Initially, three property tabs are visible - Contents, Preview and Metadata - but you can choose to show fewer than these by using the setPropertyTabs method, together with the constants whose names beign with "MASK" listed below.

You can listen for various property change events by adding a PropertyChangeListener. These events are identified by the constants whose names begin with "CHANGED" listed below.

Field Detail

CHANGED_SELECTED_NODE

public static final String CHANGED_SELECTED_NODE
identity of a property change event that is broadcast when a new node has been selected for display of properties. The oldvalue and newvalue of the PropertyChangeEvent are the TreePaths of the previously and newly selected (resp.) nodes of the tree

See Also:
Constant Field Values

CHANGED_SELECTED_TAB

public static final String CHANGED_SELECTED_TAB
identity of a property change event that is broadcast when a property panel tab has been selected. The newvalue of the PropertyChangeEvent is an Integer that contains the MASK_xxxx id of the newly selected property panel tabs, oldvalue is not supplied

setPropertyTabs

public void setPropertyTabs(int mask)
set the visibility of tabs within the property panel. You must specify the mask of all tabs you wish to be shown. Those tabs not specified in the mask will not be shown. For instance a mask of MASK_CONTENTS|MASK_METADATA will not show the Preview tab

Parameters:
mask - the logical OR of MASK_CONTENTS and/or MASK_PREVIEW and/or MASK_METADATA
